          <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Henderson-Hassel</ENAMEX>-bach equation.
          All measurements, including respiratory, haemodynamic
          <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">parameters</ENAMEX>, arterial and mixed venous <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">blood gas</ENAMEX> analyses,
          and gastric pH 
          i , were taken at baseline and
          following ventilation for <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">45 min</TIMEX> at each level of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">PEEP</ENAMEX>.
          Haemodynamic parameters were monitored continuously using
          an <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Horizon XL</ENAMEX> monitor (<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Mennen Medical Inc.</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">New York</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">NY</ENAMEX>,
          <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">USA</ENAMEX>). Cardiac output was measured in triplicate by
          <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">thermodilution</ENAMEX> technique using <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">10</NUMEX> ml saline solution at
          room temperature. <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Cardiac</ENAMEX> index, shunt fraction, oxygen
          delivery (DO 
          <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">2</NUMEX> ) and <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">oxygen</ENAMEX> consumption were
          calculated at baseline and at all <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">PEEP</ENAMEX> levels.
        
        
          Statistical analysis
          Paired analysis of variance tests were used to analyze
          the differences between measurements. 
          <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">P < 0.05</ENAMEX> was considered
          statistically significant. All values are presented as
          mean ± standard deviation.
        
      
      
